Ovid.cite('https://www.theguardian.com/technology/2012/aug/02/facebook-share-price-slumps-20-dollars',
'fake names cause the share price to drop')%].</p>

<p>The privacy issue hits Facebook again and again and again. For many people,
it's their number one reason for wanting to find another GPSN. Zuckerberg has
gone from [%
Ovid.cite('https://www.theguardian.com/technology/2010/jan/11/facebook-privacy',
'privacy is no longer a "social norm"')%], to insisting Facebook would become
a [%
Ovid.cite('https://www.theverge.com/2019/4/30/18524188/facebook-f8-keynote-mark-zuckerberg-privacy-future-2019',
'"privacy-focused communications platform"') %]. Given Zuckerberg's history,
he's more likely to be known as "the boy who cried privacy."</p>

<p>Of course, given all of the scandals, why doesn't the board simply fire
Zuckerberg as CEO and move in a new direction? Because they can't. [%
Ovid.cite('https://www.cnbc.com/2018/12/05/why-mark-zuckerberg-wont-step-down-as-facebook-chairman.html',
